{
  "texts": [
    "Posts on this forum had the benefit of including symptoms from a layperson's perspective without including additional information that laypeople do not have access to when making these decisions (e.g., results from physical examinations or lab tests).",
    "The posts also ensured that cases are phrased the way laypeople would describe them.",
    "For our research, we used Reddit's API to extract all new posts within a 14-day period, from June 16th to June 29th 2023.",
    "Recognizing that the symptom distribution in these cases might differ from those typically entered into SAAs, we applied Brunswik's second approach to achieving representative stimuli, known as 'canvassing' 21.",
    "To this end, we established quotas based on symptom clusters commonly input into SAAs."
  ]
}